# Mail Server Setup Guide (Ubuntu 26.04 LTS)

This document describes the complete setup of the mail server running on Ubuntu using:

- Postfix (SMTP)
- Dovecot (IMAP)
- Let's Encrypt (SSL/TLS)
- Nginx
- Brevo SMTP Relay (Outgoing Mail)
- Cloudflare DNS

---

# Server Information

| Component | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Operating System | Ubuntu 26.04 LTS |
| Mail Hostname | mail.blessed.co.zw |
| Web Hostname | www.blessed.co.zw |
| SMTP Server | Postfix |
| IMAP Server | Dovecot 2.4.x |
| SSL Provider | Let's Encrypt |
| Outgoing Relay | Brevo |

---

# 1. Install Required Packages

```bash
sudo apt update

sudo apt install -y \
postfix \
dovecot-imapd \
dovecot-pop3d \
certbot \
python3-certbot-nginx \
mailutils \
openssl
```

---

# 2. DNS Configuration

## Required Records

### A Record

```
mail.blessed.co.zw -> SERVER_PUBLIC_IP
```

### MX Record

```
Host: @

Priority: 10

Value: mail.blessed.co.zw
```

### SPF

```
v=spf1 include:spf.brevo.com ip4:SERVER_PUBLIC_IP ~all
```

### DKIM

Add the DKIM record provided by Brevo.

### DMARC

```
Host: _dmarc

Value:

v=DMARC1; p=quarantine; rua=mailto:postmaster@blessed.co.zw
```

### Reverse DNS (PTR)

Configure your VPS provider's PTR record:

```
SERVER_PUBLIC_IP

↓

mail.blessed.co.zw
```

Verify:

```bash
host SERVER_PUBLIC_IP
```

---

# 3. Obtain SSL Certificate

```bash
sudo certbot --nginx \
-d mail.blessed.co.zw
```

Certificates are stored in:

```
/etc/letsencrypt/live/mail.blessed.co.zw/
```

Verify:

```bash
sudo certbot certificates
```

---

# 4. Configure Postfix

Main configuration:

```
/etc/postfix/main.cf
```

Important settings:

```ini
myhostname = mail.blessed.co.zw

myorigin = /etc/mailname

inet_interfaces = all

inet_protocols = all

mydestination =
    localhost

relayhost = [smtp-relay.brevo.com]:587

smtp_sasl_auth_enable = yes

smtp_sasl_password_maps =
    static:BREVO_LOGIN:BREVO_SMTP_KEY

smtp_sasl_security_options = noanonymous

smtp_tls_security_level = encrypt

smtp_tls_CAfile =
    /etc/ssl/certs/ca-certificates.crt

smtpd_tls_cert_file =
    /etc/letsencrypt/live/mail.blessed.co.zw/fullchain.pem

smtpd_tls_key_file =
    /etc/letsencrypt/live/mail.blessed.co.zw/privkey.pem
```

Restart:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart postfix
```

---

# 5. Configure Dovecot

Configuration:

```
/etc/dovecot/
```

Verify configuration:

```bash
sudo doveconf -n
```

Authentication:

```
passdb pam
userdb passwd
```

Mail storage:

```
Maildir
```

SSL:

```
/etc/letsencrypt/live/mail.blessed.co.zw/fullchain.pem

/etc/letsencrypt/live/mail.blessed.co.zw/privkey.pem
```

Restart:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart dovecot
```

